tire trail list [--status open|in_progress|completed|failed]\\nentire trail show <trail-id>\\nentire trail create \\\"Title\\\" [--branch <name>] [--base <branch>]\\n\\n# Trail runner\\nentire trail-runner start [--daemon] [--poll-interval 30s] [--max-concurrent 1]\\nentire trail-runner run-once\\nentire trail run <trail-id>\\n```\\n\\n## Key Types\\n\\n### Trail (`trail/trail.go`)\\n\\n```go\\ntype TrailID string  // 12-hex-char, same pattern as CheckpointID\\n\\ntype Trail struct {\\n    ID          TrailID   `json:\\\"id\\\"`\\n    Title       string    `json:\\\"title\\\"`\\n    Description string    `json:\\\"description\\\"`\\n    Branch      string    `json:\\\"branch\\\"`\\n    BaseBranch  string    `json:\\\"base_branch\\\"`\\n    AuthorID    string    `json:\\\"author_id\\\"`\\n    Assignees   []string  `json:\\\"assignees\\\"`\\n    Labels      []string  `json:\\\"labels\\\"`\\n    CreatedAt   time.Time `json:\\\"created_at\\\"`\\n    UpdatedAt   time.Time `json:\\\"updated_at\\\"`\\n}\\n\\ntype TrailState string\\nconst (\\n    TrailStateOpen       TrailState = \\\"open\\\"        // No refs\\n    TrailStateInProgress TrailState = \\\"in_progress\\\" // claimed ref exists\\n    TrailStateCompleted  TrailState = \\\"completed\\\"   // completed ref exists\\n    TrailStateFailed     TrailState = \\\"failed\\\"      // failed ref exists\\n)\\n```\\n\\n### Store (`trail/store.go`)\\n\\n```go\\ntype Store struct {\\n    repo *git.Repository\\n}\\n\\nfunc (s *Store) EnsureBranch() error                    // Create orphan branch if needed\\nfunc (s *Store) Create(ctx, *Trail) error              // Write trail to branch\\nfunc (s *Store) Get(ctx, TrailID) (*Trail, error)      // Read trail metadata\\nfunc (s *Store) List(ctx) ([]*Trail, error)            // List all trails\\n```\\n\\n### StateManager (`trail/state.go`)\\n\\n```go\\nconst RefPrefix = \\\"refs/entire/trails/\\\"\\n\\ntype StateManager struct { repo *git.Repository }\\n\\nfunc (m *StateManager) GetState(ctx, TrailID) (TrailState, error)\\nfunc (m *StateManager) Claim(ctx, TrailID) error      // Atomic - fails if exists\\nfunc (m *StateManager) Complete(ctx, TrailID) error\\nfunc (m *StateManager) Fail(ctx, TrailID) error\\nfunc (m *StateManager) Release(ctx, TrailID) error    // Remove claimed ref\\n```\\n\\n### Runner (`trail/runner.go`)\\n\\n```go\\ntype RunnerConfig struct {\\n    PollInterval  time.Duration\\n    MaxConcurrent int\\n    Daemon        bool\\n    Agent         string        // \\\"claude-code\\\"\\n    Model         string        // Optional model override\\n    Timeout       time.Duration // Per-trail timeout\\n}\\n\\ntype Runner struct {\\n    store   *Store\\n    state   *StateManager\\n    config  RunnerConfig\\n}\\n\\nfunc (r *Runner) Start(ctx) error       // Daemon mode\\nfunc (r *Runner) RunOnce(ctx) error     // Single iteration\\nfunc (r *Runner) RunTrail(ctx, TrailID) error\\n```\\n\\n## Implementation Phases\\n\\n### Phase 1: Core Types and Store\\n**Files:** `trail/trail.go`, `trail/store.go`\\n\\n1. Define `TrailID` type with validation (pattern from `checkpoint/id/id.go`)\\n2. Define `Trail` struct matching entire.io PR #738 format\\n3. Implement `Store` with branch operations:\\n   - `EnsureBranch()` - create `entire/trails` orphan branch (pattern from `checkpoint/committed.go:ensureSessionsBranch`)\\n   - `Get()` - read `<id>/metadata.json` from branch tree\\n   - `List()` - enumerate trail directories\\n   - `Create()` - write metadata.json to branch\\n\\n**Key patterns to follow:**\\n- `checkpoint/committed.go`: `getSessionsBranchEntries()`, `BuildTreeFromEntries()`\\n- `validation/validators.go`: ID validation\\n\\n### Phase 2: State Management\\n**Files:** `trail/state.go`, `trail/discovery.go`\\n\\n1. Implement ref-based state:\\n   ```go\\n   // Claim atomically\\n   ref := plumbing.NewHashReference(\\n       plumbing.ReferenceName(\\\"refs/entire/trails/\\\"+id+\\\"/claimed\\\"),\\n       branchHead,\\n   )\\n   err := repo.Storer.SetReference(ref)\\n   ```\\n\\n2. State checking via `repo.Reference()` existence\\n3. Discovery: combine `Store.List()` with state filtering\\n\\n### Phase 3: Commands\\n**Files:** `trail.go`, `trail_runner.go`, update `root.go`\\n\\n1. `entire trail list` - table output with ID, title, branch, state\\n2. `entire trail show <id>` - detailed view\\n3. `entire trail create` - interactive or flags\\n4. `entire trail-runner start` / `run-once`\\n5. `entire trail run <id>` - manual execution\\n\\n**Pattern from:** `rewind.go`, `validate.go`\\n\\n### Phase 4: Execution Engine\\n**Files:** `trail/runner.go`, `trail/worktree.go`\\n\\n1. Worktree management (git CLI):\\n   ```go\\n   exec.CommandContext(ctx, \\\"git\\\", \\\"worktree\\\", \\\"add\\\", path, branch)\\n   exec.CommandContext(ctx, \\\"git\\\", \\\"worktree\\\", \\\"remove\\\", path)\\n   ```\\n\\n2. Agent invocation (pattern from `e2e_test/agent_runner.go`):\\n   ```go\\n   cmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \\\"claude\\\", \\\"--model\\\", model, \\\"-p\\\", prompt)\\n   cmd.Dir = worktreePath\\n   ```\\n\\n3. Runner loop:\\n   - Discover open trails\\n   - Claim atomically (skip if fails)\\n   - Create worktree\\n   - Run agent with trail description\\n   - Update state on completion/failure\\n   - Cleanup worktree\\n\\n### Phase 5: Testing\\n**Files:** `trail/trail_test.go`, `integration_test/trail_test.go`\\n\\n1. Unit tests for ID validation, store CRUD, state transitions\\n2. Integration tests for end-to-end flow\\n3. Use `t.Parallel()` per CLAUDE.md guidelines\\n\\n## Critical Files to Reference\\n\\n| Purpose | File |\\n|---------|------|\\n| Orphan branch ops | `checkpoint/committed.go` |\\n| ID type pattern | `checkpoint/id/id.go` |\\n| Agent invocation | `e2e_test/agent_runner.go` |\\n| Command structure | `rewind.go` |\\n| Validation helpers | `validation/validators.go` |\\n| Worktree paths | `paths/worktree.go` |\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. **Unit tests:** `mise run test`\\n2. **Int